description: Sets the key state of a KMS key to enabled. This allows you to use the KMS key for cryptographic operations. The KMS key that you use for this operation must be in a compatible key state. For details, see Key states of KMS keys in the Key Management Service Developer Guide. Cross-account use: No. You cannot perform this operation on a KMS key in a different Amazon Web Services account. Required permissions: kms:EnableKey (key policy) Related operations:  DisableKey. Eventual consistency: The KMS API follows an eventual consistency model. For more information, see KMS eventual consistency.
